Task 3 - Ros2

I made a ROS2 workspace and learned how it is set up for this task. I made a package called distance_demo and put a simple publisher and subscriber node in it.

I used colcon build to make the workspace, and then I ran the setup file so that ROS2 could see the package. Then, I could use the ros2 run command to run the node.

This task helped me learn how packages, workspaces, and nodes in ROS2 work together. I also learned that before running any package, I need to build and source the workspace.

For your reference, I have also included screenshots of the process of installing ROS2 and setting up a dual boot on Ubuntu.
